---
const capabilities = [
  "4 recall strategies (temporal, causal, analogical, similarity)",
  "Importance-weighted storage",
  "Automatic decay & reinforcement",
  "Episode to insight consolidation",
  "Causal edge tracking",
  "Real-time memory subscriptions",
];
---

<section class="py-20 md:py-32 border-t border-border/50">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-6">
    <div class="text-center mb-16">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-4">
        One install. Your agent remembers.
      </h2>
      <p class="text-muted text-lg max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        HEBBS ships as a drop-in agent skill. Install the skill, and your agent gets cognitive memory immediately. No SDK integration. No glue code. No configuration.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 items-start">
      <!-- Install -->
      <div>
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-accent/30 bg-accent/[0.04] overflow-hidden mb-6">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-3 border-b border-accent/20">
            <div class="w-3 h-3 rounded-full bg-red/40"></div>
            <div class="w-3 h-3 rounded-full bg-accent/40"></div>
            <div class="w-3 h-3 rounded-full bg-green/40"></div>
            <span class="ml-2 text-xs text-muted font-mono">terminal</span>
          </div>
          <div class="p-6">
            <pre class="font-mono text-sm"><code><span class="text-muted"># Install the server</span>
<span class="text-accent">$</span> <span class="text-text">brew install hebbs-ai/tap/hebbs</span>

<span class="text-muted"># Install the agent skill</span>
<span class="text-accent">$</span> <span class="text-text">git clone https://github.com/hebbs-ai/hebbs-skill.git /tmp/hebbs-skill</span>
<span class="text-accent">$</span> <span class="text-text">cp -r /tmp/hebbs-skill/hebbs ~/.your-agent/skills/hebbs</span>

<span class="text-green">Done.</span> <span class="text-muted">Your agent now has cognitive memory.</span></code></pre>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-xl border border-border bg-surface/40 p-5">
          <p class="text-xs font-mono text-accent uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">How it works</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-muted leading-relaxed mb-3">
            Drop the <code class="text-cyan text-xs">SKILL.md</code> file from
            <a href="https://github.com/hebbs-ai/hebbs-skill" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-accent hover:underline">github.com/hebbs-ai/hebbs-skill</a>
            into your agent's skill directory. Any agent that reads SKILL.md files will discover it automatically.
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-muted leading-relaxed">
            The skill teaches the agent to use HEBBS natively - <span class="text-text">remember</span>, <span class="text-text">recall</span>, <span class="text-text">reflect</span>, <span class="text-text">forget</span>, <span class="text-text">prime</span> - as part of its reasoning loop.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Capabilities -->
      <div class="rounded-xl border border-border bg-surface/40 p-6 md:p-8">
        <p class="text-xs font-mono text-accent uppercase tracking-wider mb-6">What your agent gets</p>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          {capabilities.map((cap) => (
            <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-accent mt-0.5 shrink-0">&#10003;</span>
              <p class="text-text text-sm">{cap}</p>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>

        <div class="border-t border-border mt-6 pt-6">
          <p class="text-xs text-muted leading-relaxed">
            The agent decides when to remember, what strategy to recall with, and when to consolidate. No developer glue code required.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
